HEADWORD: Telechirograph
<hw>Tel`e*chi"ro*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>th^le</grk> far + <grk>chei`r</grk>, <grk>cheiro`s</grk>, hand +
<ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for telegraphically
transmitting and receiving handwritten messages, as photographically by
a beam of light from a mirror.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

